They will be here!

280
00:19:40,195 --> 00:19:41,317
Who? Hey! Who?

281
00:19:41,352 --> 00:19:42,440
Who will be here?

282
00:19:42,475 --> 00:19:43,565
My money.

283
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:44,640
I thought you said
this was going to be safe.

284
00:19:44,675 --> 00:19:46,005
My money...

285
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:49,280
No. No money
until you show us.

286
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:17,645
Let's set up.

287
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:19,360
I can't shoot this, man.

288
00:20:19,395 --> 00:20:22,560
My money...

289
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:31,040
Let's set up.

290
00:20:35,115 --> 00:20:36,085
What...

291
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:39,765
What are you
doing?

292
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:41,400
I'm sorry, Matthew Ellman.

293
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:46,005
You saw?

294
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,640
Who the hell are you?

295
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:50,580
I was watching you.

296
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:56,680
The man who beat you,
do not judge him.

297
00:20:56,715 --> 00:20:58,677
Maybe you didn't hear me.

298
00:20:58,712 --> 00:21:00,576
I said who the hell are you?

299
00:21:00,611 --> 00:21:02,405
His name is
Richard Burton.

300
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:05,640
Those in power will try
to use you against him.

301
00:21:05,675 --> 00:21:06,600
Do not listen to them.

302
00:21:09,480 --> 00:21:11,725
Okay, you know what?

303
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:14,040
I'm just going to go
find some cold water

304
00:21:14,075 --> 00:21:15,325
And dip my head in it,

305
00:21:15,360 --> 00:21:16,840
And start this day
all over,

306
00:21:16,875 --> 00:21:19,077
All right, Obi-Wan?

307
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:37,840
You're that thing
I saw in the cave,

308
00:21:37,875 --> 00:21:40,040
When I was wearing
the wrist band,

309
00:21:40,075 --> 00:21:42,837
When I was basically dead.

310
00:21:42,872 --> 00:21:45,600
I'm your caretaker, Matthew.

311
00:21:45,635 --> 00:21:47,800
I am here to watch you.

312
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,520
He said he was watching me.

313
00:21:51,555 --> 00:21:53,325
Listen to me.

314
00:21:53,360 --> 00:21:55,805
He is a salvationist,
a traitor.

315
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:57,720
They have corrupted many
here in Riverworld,

316
00:21:57,755 --> 00:21:59,805
Including this man, Burton.

317
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:03,760
I'm sorry, but you guys
can fight your own war.

318
00:22:03,795 --> 00:22:05,257
I've got someone I need to find.

319
00:22:05,292 --> 00:22:06,720
If you wish to find Jessica...

320
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:11,200
Then you must first
stop Burton,

321
00:22:11,235 --> 00:22:13,760
Even if it means killing him.

322
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:20,765
No...

323
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:24,120
You can't do that!

324
00:22:24,155 --> 00:22:25,205
You are hurt.

325
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:27,240
Did you see
that thing?

326
00:22:27,275 --> 00:22:28,405
I saw nothing.

327
00:22:28,440 --> 00:22:30,100
I heard you talking.

328
00:22:30,135 --> 00:22:31,725
I was looking for you.

329
00:22:31,760 --> 00:22:33,960
I'm not even sure
it was human.

330
00:22:33,995 --> 00:22:36,280
You saw an oni?

331
00:22:36,315 --> 00:22:38,805
A demon?

332
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:41,120
Oni, alien,
bart simpson,

333
00:22:41,155 --> 00:22:43,437
I have no idea.

334
00:22:45,760 --> 00:22:47,400
I've got to get some
answers from someone.

335
00:22:47,435 --> 00:22:49,205
You need to rest.

336
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:52,000
You are fortunate
to be alive.

337
00:22:52,035 --> 00:22:55,240
Yeah, if we are alive.

338
00:22:56,800 --> 00:22:58,740
Does your head hurt?

339
00:22:58,775 --> 00:23:00,645
It's killing me.

340
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:04,040
If you can feel pain,
then you're alive,

341
00:23:04,075 --> 00:23:05,805
And if you're alive,

342
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:08,200
Then perhaps
we all are.

343
00:23:24,120 --> 00:23:25,920
Oh, feels good!

344
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:48,440
We lost one of
our own tonight.

345
00:23:48,475 --> 00:23:50,485
We must be cautious.

346
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:54,440
There are second chances
everywhere.

347
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:58,840
You were unwise to provoke
Mr. Ellman so soon.

348
00:23:58,875 --> 00:24:00,725
Why?

349
00:24:00,760 --> 00:24:02,285
He has been chosen.

350
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:03,460
He's not wearing a band.

351
00:24:03,495 --> 00:24:04,565
He's looking for the girl.

352
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:05,960
Everything puts him
in opposition to me.

353
00:24:05,995 --> 00:24:07,117
I say get rid of him,

354
00:24:07,152 --> 00:24:08,205
Sooner rather than later.

355
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:10,600
Not while
he's being observed...

356
00:24:10,635 --> 00:24:12,805
And protected,

357
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:15,680
And he's not yet had time
to make a judgement.

358
00:24:15,715 --> 00:24:17,960
Perhaps he will
come around to your way.

359
00:24:17,995 --> 00:24:22,085
Not with the girl between us.

360
00:24:22,120 --> 00:24:24,160
Then let him lead you
back to her,

361
00:24:24,195 --> 00:24:25,520
And perhaps the tower.

362
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:29,680
And when you have it
within your sights,

363
00:24:29,715 --> 00:24:32,360
Do what you must.

364
00:24:40,760 --> 00:24:42,920
How many times?

365
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:47,080
How many times have you ridden
the suicide express, huh?

366
00:24:47,115 --> 00:24:48,217
Me?

367
00:24:48,252 --> 00:24:49,285
Four!

368
00:24:49,320 --> 00:24:50,980
Four times I've killed myself.

369
00:24:51,015 --> 00:24:52,867
That, comrades, is courage.

370
00:24:52,902 --> 00:24:54,720
That, comrades, is stupidity.

371
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,600
Because one time
you won't come back,

372
00:24:58,635 --> 00:25:01,000
And no one knows
when that time may be.

373
00:25:01,035 --> 00:25:02,245
Never do anything

374
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:05,120
For which the outcome
is uncertain.

375
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:12,045
Now, wait for me here.

376
00:25:12,080 --> 00:25:13,440
Tomorrow,
we meet our friend,

377
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:15,560
And, God-willing,
we'll begin our journey.

378
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:41,920
So, what was his name?

379
00:25:44,360 --> 00:25:45,485
A woman like you

380
00:25:45,520 --> 00:25:48,000
Doesn't just suddenly
decide to become a nun.

381
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:56,100
Yoshinaka,

382
00:25:56,135 --> 00:25:58,645
A samurai.

383
00:25:58,680 --> 00:26:01,725
He was a great man,

384
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:04,400
But also an ambitious man,

385
00:26:04,435 --> 00:26:07,040
And to achieve
his ambitions,

386
00:26:07,075 --> 00:26:10,177
He waged a war.

387
00:26:10,212 --> 00:26:13,280
Many people died.

388
00:26:13,315 --> 00:26:15,520
He died.

389
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:20,520
He was my greatest mistake.

390
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:23,600
What was yours?

391
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:29,840
There was more than just one.

392
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,525
"the road we walk

393
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:38,840
Was built with the stones
that scar our feet."

394
00:26:38,875 --> 00:26:41,120
Who said that?

395
00:26:41,155 --> 00:26:42,085
Buddha?

396
00:26:42,120 --> 00:26:46,725
A nun from near kyoto,

397
00:26:46,760 --> 00:26:51,120
In the years
after the gempei wars.

398
00:26:53,280 --> 00:26:57,165
I was a...

399
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:59,220
A television
reporter

400
00:26:59,255 --> 00:27:01,240
During our
times of war.

401
00:27:03,840 --> 00:27:05,460
I had a buddy,

402
00:27:05,495 --> 00:27:07,045
A cameraman.

403
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:10,640
We used a machine
to take pictures of places,

404
00:27:10,675 --> 00:27:13,897
People who had been
hurt by others.

405
00:27:13,932 --> 00:27:17,085
I'm not explaining
myself very well.

406
00:27:17,120 --> 00:27:21,400
You painted portraits
and told true stories.

407
00:27:21,435 --> 00:27:26,205
Yeah, most of the time,

408
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:29,360
And you got it right,
you were a hero.

409
00:27:29,395 --> 00:27:30,485
Wrong...

410
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:33,740
To live an honorable life,

411
00:27:33,775 --> 00:27:36,960
One must risk everything,

412
00:27:36,995 --> 00:27:38,400
Always.

413
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:43,325
Tomoe...

414
00:27:43,360 --> 00:27:46,485
This samurai of yours,

415
00:27:46,520 --> 00:27:49,600
If he had to kill a man,
a stranger, to save you,

416
00:27:49,635 --> 00:27:51,757
Would he have done it?

417
00:27:51,792 --> 00:27:53,880
Without hesitation.

418
00:27:56,760 --> 00:27:59,320
I need to find this man, Burton,

419
00:27:59,355 --> 00:28:01,280
The one who attacked me.

420
00:28:01,315 --> 00:28:03,920
To kill him.

421
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:09,725
You...

422
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:11,160
You, get over here!

423
00:28:11,195 --> 00:28:12,165
Matthew!

424
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:13,165
You killed us!

425
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:14,245
You killed all of us!

426
00:28:14,280 --> 00:28:15,200
Stop!
You're hurting her!

427
00:28:15,235 --> 00:28:17,257
I'm sorry...

428
00:28:17,292 --> 00:28:18,946
I'm sorry!

429
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:21,600
I survived
Afghanistan,

430
00:28:21,635 --> 00:28:24,045
Chechnya, Darfur,

431
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:25,880
And this coward kills me

432
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:27,640
And the only woman
I ever truly loved!

433
00:28:27,675 --> 00:28:31,160
I'm sorry!

434
00:28:32,960 --> 00:28:35,820
I'm sorry...

435
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:51,880
They told me
you were devils,

436
00:28:51,915 --> 00:28:53,365
Unclean,

437
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:54,525
That by killing you

438
00:28:54,560 --> 00:28:56,205
I would free
our people,

439
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:59,320
That I'd be rewarded
in paradise.

440
00:28:59,355 --> 00:29:03,000
But there is no paradise,

441
00:29:03,035 --> 00:29:04,525
Only this place,

442
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:06,685
This land
of infidels.

443
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:08,760
So, because you didn't
get your reward,

444
00:29:08,795 --> 00:29:10,765
You're suddenly sorry
for what you did?

445
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:14,880
If they lied about paradise,
what else did they lie about?

446
00:29:14,915 --> 00:29:17,800
How is a person
supposed to live

447
00:29:17,835 --> 00:29:21,880
When everything
is a lie?

448
00:29:21,915 --> 00:29:23,405
Soldiers!

449
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:29,080
Who the hell
are these guys?

450
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:32,525
Conquistadors.

451
00:29:32,560 --> 00:29:34,605
That's a spanish flag.

452
00:29:34,640 --> 00:29:35,640
All right, honey,
you stay here.

453
00:29:35,675 --> 00:29:36,605
No!

454
00:29:36,640 --> 00:29:37,680
No, no, no,
I'll handle these clowns.

455
00:29:37,715 --> 00:29:38,680
Hey! Hey, you!

456
00:29:38,715 --> 00:29:39,480
Daniel...

457
00:29:40,760 --> 00:29:43,245
Hey, what are
you doing?

458
00:29:43,280 --> 00:29:45,400
You guys can't just
waltz in here.

459
00:29:45,435 --> 00:29:46,360
That's enough.

460
00:29:47,400 --> 00:29:48,520
Hey, hey, hey,
who are you guys?

461
00:29:48,555 --> 00:29:49,725
Huh? What's going on?

462
00:29:52,280 --> 00:29:53,720
You will not address
El Adelantado

463
00:29:53,755 --> 00:29:54,800
Without permission,
peasant.

464
00:29:56,400 --> 00:29:57,480
Okay, shorty, listen,

465
00:29:57,515 --> 00:29:58,525
I'm an american attorney,

466
00:29:58,560 --> 00:30:00,360
And I'll address
whoever I damn well please,

467
00:30:00,395 --> 00:30:02,160
Including the,
man of La Mancha here.

468
00:30:02,195 --> 00:30:03,277
Nice outfit...

469
00:30:04,360 --> 00:30:05,920
No, you will be
slaughtered!

470
00:30:05,955 --> 00:30:07,320
Silencio.

471
00:30:08,760 --> 00:30:09,840
Daniel!

472
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:12,480
No! No!

473
00:30:17,755 --> 00:30:19,725
You will all bow down

474
00:30:19,760 --> 00:30:22,520
To your new lord and master!

475
00:30:27,320 --> 00:30:30,360
May I present
the governor-general of Peru,

476
00:30:30,395 --> 00:30:32,600
Conqueror of the incas,

477
00:30:32,635 --> 00:30:34,240
Francisco Pizarro.

478
00:30:34,275 --> 00:30:37,560
Pizarro?

479
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:45,680
Heed the words
of El Adelantado!

480
00:30:45,715 --> 00:30:49,085
Poor ignorant bastards.

481
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:51,300
You have no idea where you are,

482
00:30:51,335 --> 00:30:53,445
Or what is happening to you.

483
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:57,640
I will make everything
simple, huh?

484
00:30:57,675 --> 00:30:59,405
Clear.

485
00:30:59,440 --> 00:31:00,805
This world,

486
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:03,180
This Riverworld,

487
00:31:03,215 --> 00:31:05,485
Is a purgatory,

488
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:07,245
Constructed
by demons,

489
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:10,120
And overrun by pagans
and idolaters,

490
00:31:10,155 --> 00:31:11,805
Not so different

491
00:31:11,840 --> 00:31:13,240
From the depraved
savages

492
00:31:13,275 --> 00:31:16,005
Of the americas

493
00:31:16,040 --> 00:31:18,840
Before we spaniards
brought them to heel.

494
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:22,520
What this world
needs

495
00:31:22,555 --> 00:31:25,005
Is vision.

496
00:31:25,040 --> 00:31:27,400
It needs order.

497
00:31:27,435 --> 00:31:29,725
I have that vision,

498
00:31:29,760 --> 00:31:34,400
And I will provide
that order,

499
00:31:34,435 --> 00:31:35,977
And you,

500
00:31:36,012 --> 00:31:37,485
All of you,

501
00:31:37,520 --> 00:31:41,520
Will help me
in this divine mission,

502
00:31:41,555 --> 00:31:43,725
Or...

503
00:31:43,760 --> 00:31:46,320
I will make you
suffer

504
00:31:46,355 --> 00:31:48,880
Until you beg
for death.

505
00:31:57,160 --> 00:31:58,205
Matthew...

506
00:31:58,240 --> 00:32:02,085
Your wound,
it is healed.

507
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:04,600
Things must
heal quickly here.

508
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:21,205
Show your grailband,

509
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:24,440
And remember,
one third of your food is ours.

510
00:32:24,475 --> 00:32:27,640
Anyone taking alcohol
or drugs from the stone

511
00:32:27,675 --> 00:32:28,725
Will be punished.

512
00:32:28,760 --> 00:32:31,620
Well, this just keeps
getting better.

513
00:32:31,655 --> 00:32:34,480
I'm almost glad
Antonio's not here...

514
00:32:34,515 --> 00:32:35,885
Almost.

515
00:32:35,920 --> 00:32:37,260
We have to get away.

516
00:32:37,295 --> 00:32:38,547
Too many soldiers.

517
00:32:38,582 --> 00:32:39,765
We must be
patient,

518
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:42,365
Wait for
an opportunity.

519
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:45,480
Oh, hey,
your grailband.

520
00:32:45,515 --> 00:32:46,645
Why don't you get lost?

521
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:48,960
We'll scrape up
enough to feed you.

522
00:32:48,995 --> 00:32:51,360
You, come with me!

523
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:54,240
This way, move!

524
00:32:58,440 --> 00:32:59,960
Where are you
taking me?

525
00:32:59,995 --> 00:33:03,560
What did I do wrong?

526
00:33:06,320 --> 00:33:08,140
Antonio?

527
00:33:08,175 --> 00:33:09,925
Oh, my God!

528
00:33:09,960 --> 00:33:11,725
You're alive.
Thank God!

529
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:12,880
There's too much
to explain right now.

530
00:33:12,915 --> 00:33:13,880
We have to be
very careful.

531
00:33:13,915 --> 00:33:15,445
Just know

532
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:18,040
That I'm going to find a way
to get us out of here, okay?

533
00:33:18,075 --> 00:33:19,845
Okay?

534
00:33:19,880 --> 00:33:21,080
Do you get to keep the uniform?

535
00:33:23,800 --> 00:33:26,360
18 months
I've been looking for you.

536
00:33:26,395 --> 00:33:28,085
I'd almost given up hope.

537
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:29,560
A year and a half?
How is that possible?

538
00:33:31,520 --> 00:33:34,445
Welcome to Riverworld.

539
00:33:34,480 --> 00:33:35,760
I hope you like
mac and cheese.

540
00:33:35,795 --> 00:33:37,040
Are you kidding?
Comfort food.

541
00:33:37,075 --> 00:33:39,245
Thanks.

542
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:40,820
Work harder!

543
00:33:40,855 --> 00:33:42,325
Antonio...

544
00:33:42,360 --> 00:33:43,720
How many people did you
see in your travels?

545
00:33:43,755 --> 00:33:44,725
Thousands.

546
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:45,920
I think people
from all across time

547
00:33:45,955 --> 00:33:47,080
Are constantly
being resurrected

548
00:33:47,115 --> 00:33:48,280
On these riverbanks.

549
00:33:48,315 --> 00:33:49,477
But why?

550
00:33:49,512 --> 00:33:50,605
Why?

551
00:33:50,640 --> 00:33:51,885
Beats me.

552
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:53,040
But there has to
be some logic,

553
00:33:53,075 --> 00:33:54,245
Some connection,

554
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:55,520
Or none of us would
have found each other.

555
00:33:55,555 --> 00:33:57,205
Look, the only thing I know is

556
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:59,200
We've got to find a way
to get out of here.

557
00:33:59,235 --> 00:34:01,805
You, beat it!

558
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:03,380
Some kind of ship's
coming upriver.

559
00:34:03,415 --> 00:34:04,727
Pizarro's been
chasing it for years.

560
00:34:04,762 --> 00:34:06,040
He's going to ambush it
from this fort.

561
00:34:06,075 --> 00:34:07,525
This is good.

562
00:34:07,560 --> 00:34:10,200
When the fighting starts,
we can run.

563
00:34:10,235 --> 00:34:12,840
There will be much
chaos and confusion.

564
00:34:12,875 --> 00:34:13,885
In the meantime,

565
00:34:13,920 --> 00:34:14,920
We've got to do
whatever we can

566
00:34:14,955 --> 00:34:16,045
To screw this guy.

567
00:34:16,080 --> 00:34:18,320
That means we work slow,
we make mistakes,

568
00:34:18,355 --> 00:34:19,440
We sabotage weapons...

569
00:34:21,280 --> 00:34:22,620
That one.

570
00:34:22,655 --> 00:34:23,925
Arrest him.

571
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:26,480
You heard the man.

572
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:43,840
Please,
sit down.

573
00:34:43,875 --> 00:34:45,720
I'm fine standing.

574
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:48,760
Sitting's good.

575
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:53,560
Show me your wrist.

576
00:34:55,080 --> 00:34:56,560
Peramo.

577
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:00,840
Unbound, huh?

578
00:35:00,875 --> 00:35:03,445
Like me.

579
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:12,085
You don't look like
a soldier, but...

580
00:35:12,120 --> 00:35:16,360
I am told you have been
through many battles.

581
00:35:16,395 --> 00:35:18,880
I was a war zone reporter.

582
00:35:18,915 --> 00:35:20,325
That's a man who...

583
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:22,205
I know what a reporter is, huh?

584
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:24,080
All the time crying to the world
about the weak.

585
00:35:24,115 --> 00:35:26,560
But there have
always been weak, huh?

586
00:35:26,595 --> 00:35:27,885
And strong.

587
00:35:27,920 --> 00:35:29,560
Which are you, senor Ellman?

588
00:35:29,595 --> 00:35:32,285
Which should I be?

589
00:35:32,320 --> 00:35:33,840
If I'm weak,
you'll take advantage.

590
00:35:33,875 --> 00:35:35,557
If I'm strong, I'm a threat,

591
00:35:35,592 --> 00:35:37,240
And you might have me killed.

592
00:35:41,375 --> 00:35:43,565
Very clever.

593
00:35:43,600 --> 00:35:44,725
You're american, si?

594
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:47,720
I have seen far
too many americans

595
00:35:47,755 --> 00:35:50,457
Since I have
arrived here, huh?

596
00:35:50,492 --> 00:35:53,125
Oh, so noble in their hearts,

597
00:35:53,160 --> 00:35:55,640
But they have
no concept of glory,

598
00:35:55,675 --> 00:35:58,085
Only an overweening
selfishness.

599
00:35:58,120 --> 00:36:02,120
They want everyone
to be just like them.

600
00:36:02,155 --> 00:36:04,557
They are children.

601
00:36:04,592 --> 00:36:06,925
They are not men.

602
00:36:06,960 --> 00:36:09,845
This may surprise you,

603
00:36:09,880 --> 00:36:12,760
But history
didn't treat you kindly.

604
00:36:12,795 --> 00:36:13,897
Are we through?

605
00:36:13,932 --> 00:36:15,586
Please, please.

606
00:36:15,621 --> 00:36:16,970
Be patient, huh?

607
00:36:17,005 --> 00:36:18,285
You're my guest.

608
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:20,925
You see, I'm curious,
senor Ellman,

609
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:22,960
Where is it that you think
that you are going?

610
00:36:22,995 --> 00:36:25,325
Have you a plan,

611
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:28,005
A destination
in mind?

612
00:36:28,040 --> 00:36:30,800
Or are you
looking for something?

613
00:36:30,835 --> 00:36:32,765
Or someone?

614
00:36:32,800 --> 00:36:34,920
Did Burton tell you that?

615
00:36:34,955 --> 00:36:36,777
Ah, you know my new friend.

616
00:36:36,812 --> 00:36:38,565
Burton doesn't strike me

617
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:40,080
As the kind of man
who makes friends.

618
00:36:40,115 --> 00:36:41,005
No.

619
00:36:41,040 --> 00:36:43,960
No, but we are brothers,
of a sort,

620
00:36:43,995 --> 00:36:46,217
Burton and I, huh?

621
00:36:46,252 --> 00:36:48,405
The question is,

622
00:36:48,440 --> 00:36:50,285
Whose brother are you?

623
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:52,840
I don't know what you mean.

624
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:58,920
You're unbound.

625
00:36:58,955 --> 00:37:01,405
No grailband, huh?

626
00:37:01,440 --> 00:37:05,880
But you must have been helped
somewhere along the way, huh?

627
00:37:05,915 --> 00:37:07,805
Was it a...

628
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:09,160
Was it a man or a woman?

629
00:37:10,720 --> 00:37:12,780
Look, I woke up here yesterday.

630
00:37:12,815 --> 00:37:14,840
I don't know anything
about sides.

631
00:37:17,080 --> 00:37:19,800
I could end you,
senor Ellman,

632
00:37:19,835 --> 00:37:22,520
Like I have ended
so many others...

633
00:37:22,555 --> 00:37:24,085
Emperors,
noblemen.

634
00:37:24,120 --> 00:37:25,440
Your blood would be
little more

635
00:37:25,475 --> 00:37:26,800
Than an insignificant drop

636
00:37:26,835 --> 00:37:30,485
In a vast red sea.

637
00:37:30,520 --> 00:37:34,360
You can kill me,
but I'll come back, won't I?

638
00:37:34,395 --> 00:37:37,437
Just like you
and everyone else here.

639
00:37:37,472 --> 00:37:40,445
I haven't seen anyone
really old.

640
00:37:40,480 --> 00:37:43,400
Do you just kill yourself
and start again?

641
00:37:43,435 --> 00:37:44,325
Is that the secret?

642
00:37:44,360 --> 00:37:47,360
There are
endless secrets

643
00:37:47,395 --> 00:37:50,457
Within secrets,

644
00:37:50,492 --> 00:37:53,485
None of which

645
00:37:53,520 --> 00:37:56,800
You have earned
the right to know, hmm?

646
00:37:56,835 --> 00:37:58,400
Best I keep
an eye on you.

647
00:37:58,435 --> 00:38:01,200
Put him in irons.

648
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:14,160
Where did they take Matt?

649
00:38:14,195 --> 00:38:15,365
I'll find Matt.

650
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:17,520
Just keep doing your dirty work,
but don't get caught.

651
00:38:17,555 --> 00:38:21,160
Work harder or starve!

652
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:42,405
Bernardo, come!

653
00:38:42,440 --> 00:38:43,280
I have to show you something.

654
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:43,365
Thank you.

655
00:39:43,400 --> 00:39:44,485
Thank you very much.

656
00:39:44,520 --> 00:39:46,440
Haven't had a nice meal
of knuckles and dirt

657
00:39:46,475 --> 00:39:48,640
Since my last
birthday,

658
00:39:48,680 --> 00:39:50,320
You son
of a bitches.

659
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:54,720
Our first category
is "three strikes."

660
00:39:54,755 --> 00:39:56,765
For 200 dollars,

661
00:39:56,800 --> 00:39:58,845
"these three outings

662
00:39:58,880 --> 00:40:01,800
Should never
have been undertaken."

663
00:40:01,835 --> 00:40:04,640
What is
the titanic,

664
00:40:04,675 --> 00:40:07,045
The hindenberg,

665
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:08,720
And Matt Ellman's
new year's eve party

666
00:40:08,755 --> 00:40:10,280
On the staten island
ferry!

667
00:40:10,315 --> 00:40:11,440
Come here.

668
00:40:11,475 --> 00:40:14,080
Look at you!

669
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:19,200
It's good to see you, man.

670
00:40:20,320 --> 00:40:22,240
Last glimpse I had of you,

671
00:40:22,275 --> 00:40:24,160
You were lying in your coffin.

672
00:40:25,480 --> 00:40:26,685
Sorry, man.

673
00:40:26,720 --> 00:40:27,760
I'm sorry for
staring at you.

674
00:40:27,795 --> 00:40:29,357
I just can't
believe it's you.

675
00:40:29,392 --> 00:40:30,920
Matt Ellman
is in the house!

676
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:37,565
What are you
doing here?

677
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:40,320
Oh, that's a sorry,
sorry story.

678
00:40:40,355 --> 00:40:42,245
I had four numbers

679
00:40:42,280 --> 00:40:44,420
When this thing
went down.

680
00:40:44,455 --> 00:40:46,560
I never got
to see a fifth.

681
00:40:46,595 --> 00:40:48,240
What went down?

682
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:51,920
The world, I think.

683
00:40:53,520 --> 00:40:54,685
What are you talking about?

684
00:40:54,720 --> 00:40:58,400
I was monitoring
my police scanner,

685
00:40:58,435 --> 00:41:00,177
And there was
lots of chatter.

686
00:41:00,212 --> 00:41:01,786
They scrambled
f-16s, man.

687
00:41:01,821 --> 00:41:03,360
It was bad juju,
really bad.

688
00:41:05,160 --> 00:41:06,720
You're serious?

689
00:41:06,755 --> 00:41:08,485
Yeah.

690
00:41:08,520 --> 00:41:11,245
Nasa was monitoring some ufo,

691
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:14,120
And then it vaporized
the entire earth.

692
00:41:14,155 --> 00:41:15,565
When?

693
00:41:15,600 --> 00:41:18,765
Six years after you died.

694
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:21,280
You died
six years after singapore?

695
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:25,800
So, you've just been wandering
this whole time?

696
00:41:25,835 --> 00:41:28,040
Yeah.

697
00:41:29,280 --> 00:41:31,165
Simon...

698
00:41:31,200 --> 00:41:32,600
Have you seen her?

699
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:36,885
Jessie...

700
00:41:36,920 --> 00:41:37,885
I heard she was upriver

701
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:40,440
Running from this guy
named Burton.

702
00:41:40,475 --> 00:41:42,925
Look, I tried
to find her, man,

703
00:41:42,960 --> 00:41:45,160
But I kept on running into
this dude and his men,

704
00:41:45,195 --> 00:41:46,765
And they killed me.

705
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:48,480
I'm not talking about
a bunch of clowns

706
00:41:48,515 --> 00:41:52,000
Who slayed me
with their humour.

707
00:41:52,035 --> 00:41:52,880
I'm sorry.

708
00:41:54,480 --> 00:41:55,920
You've died again, here?

709
00:41:55,955 --> 00:41:57,805
Twice.

710
00:41:57,840 --> 00:41:59,840
So we do keep coming back...

711
00:42:01,200 --> 00:42:02,960
Yeah, but I don't recommend it.

712
00:42:08,600 --> 00:42:12,000
Dude, I'm so glad
you're here.

713
00:42:13,760 --> 00:42:15,360
You too, buddy.

714
00:42:15,395 --> 00:42:16,917
Yeah.

715
00:42:28,200 --> 00:42:29,925
Damn.

716
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:30,880
Another
accident?

717
00:42:32,640 --> 00:42:33,960
Flooded ditches,
cracked oil drums,

718
00:42:33,995 --> 00:42:35,125
Loose support beams.

719
00:42:35,160 --> 00:42:36,920
It's astonishing
how many things have gone wrong

720
00:42:36,955 --> 00:42:39,520
With this little project.

721
00:42:39,555 --> 00:42:41,245
What do
you want?

722
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:43,125
A stroll along the thames,

723
00:42:43,160 --> 00:42:45,720
And a maxim gun
with a few thousand rounds,

724
00:42:45,755 --> 00:42:46,957
And a night with a hindi girl

725
00:42:46,992 --> 00:42:48,125
Well-versed in the Kama Sutra.

726
00:42:48,160 --> 00:42:49,600
Unfortunately,
I have to make do with you

727
00:42:49,635 --> 00:42:51,765
And the rest of
your sorry lot.

728
00:42:51,800 --> 00:42:52,840
I know you think
you're being very clever

729
00:42:52,875 --> 00:42:54,440
With this sabotage of yours,

730
00:42:54,475 --> 00:42:55,965
But the problem is

731
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:57,760
That each misstep you make
is going to be taken

732
00:42:57,795 --> 00:43:01,257
Out of your dear
Mr. Ellman's flesh,

733
00:43:01,292 --> 00:43:04,720
And, yes, you will
be there to watch.

734
00:43:04,755 --> 00:43:06,485
Take him away,

735
00:43:06,520 --> 00:43:09,120
And bring me
Mr. Ellman.

736
00:43:23,220 --> 00:43:24,345
Senor Ellman,

737
00:43:24,380 --> 00:43:26,340
Have you ever heard of
diego de almagro?

738
00:43:26,375 --> 00:43:28,300
Diego and I were
brothers-in-arms, huh?

739
00:43:28,335 --> 00:43:29,465
Amigos.

740
00:43:29,500 --> 00:43:31,280
Together, we conquered
the inca empire,

741
00:43:31,315 --> 00:43:33,060
Laid low atahualpa,
and shook the word.

742
00:43:33,095 --> 00:43:35,420
But when
the king made me

743
00:43:35,455 --> 00:43:37,825
Emperor of Peru,

744
00:43:37,860 --> 00:43:40,140
Diego, he became
jealous, huh?

745
00:43:40,175 --> 00:43:41,220
And he betrayed me.

746
00:43:43,060 --> 00:43:44,425
Should I be taking notes?

747
00:43:44,460 --> 00:43:46,540
Cause if there's
going to be a quiz...

748
00:43:48,332 --> 00:43:50,020
I thought perhaps

749
00:43:50,060 --> 00:43:52,660
His fate will be
illustrative.

750
00:43:52,695 --> 00:43:54,817
I rebuilt my army,

751
00:43:54,852 --> 00:43:56,905
Freed my brothers,

752
00:43:56,940 --> 00:43:58,425
Laid siege to his city,

753
00:43:58,460 --> 00:44:00,420
And defeated the cur in battle,

754
00:44:00,455 --> 00:44:02,825
And diego...

755
