He begged
for his miserable life.

756
00:44:07,175 --> 00:44:09,105
He cried like a woman

757
00:44:09,140 --> 00:44:12,465
As I slowly
strangled him to death.

758
00:44:12,500 --> 00:44:16,020
Well, there'll be no crying
here, my friend.

759
00:44:16,055 --> 00:44:17,145
Burn him alive.

760
00:44:17,180 --> 00:44:20,180
El Adelantado, a word.

761
00:44:25,260 --> 00:44:27,220
Don't kill him,
not yet.

762
00:44:27,255 --> 00:44:28,265
Why not?

763
00:44:28,300 --> 00:44:29,225
What will happen?

764
00:44:29,260 --> 00:44:30,345
You tell me now, Burton,

765
00:44:30,380 --> 00:44:31,620
Or I throw you
on the pyre with him!

766
00:44:31,655 --> 00:44:32,745
He has
no grailband.

767
00:44:32,780 --> 00:44:35,625
Draw your own
conclusion.

768
00:44:35,660 --> 00:44:39,020
You think I have friends
with the caretakers...

769
00:44:42,700 --> 00:44:44,940
What does he know
of this?

770
00:44:44,975 --> 00:44:46,505
Probably nothing,

771
00:44:46,540 --> 00:44:48,620
But I suggest
we keep him alive

772
00:44:48,655 --> 00:44:51,500
Till we know.

773
00:44:57,100 --> 00:44:59,665
Senor Ellman...

774
00:44:59,700 --> 00:45:02,140
Please forgive me, huh?

775
00:45:02,175 --> 00:45:04,217
I am but a...

776
00:45:04,252 --> 00:45:06,225
Barbarian.

777
00:45:06,260 --> 00:45:09,460
Bernardo, show our friend
to our finest...

778
00:45:09,495 --> 00:45:10,420
Accommodations.

779
00:46:14,500 --> 00:46:16,180
I can't shoot this, man.

780
00:46:18,900 --> 00:46:20,700
My money...

781
00:46:26,380 --> 00:46:28,660
Let's set up.

782
00:46:31,060 --> 00:46:32,600
Simon, let's go.

783
00:46:32,635 --> 00:46:33,887
Let's get this done.

784
00:46:33,922 --> 00:46:35,140
No, you leave now.

785
00:46:35,175 --> 00:46:38,105
Men coming.

786
00:46:38,140 --> 00:46:39,740
This is
what we came for.

787
00:46:39,775 --> 00:46:40,985
You got your money.

788
00:46:41,020 --> 00:46:42,820
The guy said let's go,
so let's go.

789
00:46:42,855 --> 00:46:45,057
He's lying, okay?

790
00:46:45,092 --> 00:46:47,225
Do you see anything?

791
00:46:47,260 --> 00:46:49,860
Let's do this.

792
00:46:54,900 --> 00:46:56,945
This is Matt Ellman.

793
00:46:56,980 --> 00:46:58,380
I'm standing in front of
a mass grave

794
00:46:58,415 --> 00:46:59,780
Here in the mountains
of chechnya...

795
00:47:54,395 --> 00:47:56,265
Simon!

796
00:47:56,300 --> 00:47:59,585
Simon...

797
00:48:01,535 --> 00:48:03,425
Simon...

798
00:48:04,975 --> 00:48:06,277
Simon?

