00:50:45,180 --> 00:50:46,780
What do you know about Sam?

834
00:50:50,340 --> 00:50:52,980
What do you know about Sam?

835
00:50:56,020 --> 00:50:57,580
What do you know
about Sam?

836
00:51:01,940 --> 00:51:02,865
Run!

837
00:51:04,315 --> 00:51:05,660
Run free!

838
00:51:05,695 --> 00:51:06,797
No!

839
00:51:06,832 --> 00:51:07,900
No!

840
00:51:14,580 --> 00:51:16,780
Risoner escaped!

841
00:51:16,815 --> 00:51:18,980
Prisoner e escaped!

842
00:51:20,300 --> 00:51:21,660
Sword.

843
00:51:57,340 --> 00:52:00,060
Get out of my way!

844
00:52:18,620 --> 00:52:21,345
Fire!

845
00:52:32,380 --> 00:52:34,300
Fall back!

846
00:52:43,340 --> 00:52:45,460
Stop!

847
00:52:54,180 --> 00:52:55,620
No grailband.

848
00:52:57,860 --> 00:52:59,900
Are you Sam?

849
00:53:15,780 --> 00:53:17,360
Launch ahead.

850
00:53:17,395 --> 00:53:18,905
Dead slow.

851
00:53:18,940 --> 00:53:21,380
Linesmen to starboard.

852
00:53:32,540 --> 00:53:34,900
Youseff, how many times
do we have to tell you,

853
00:53:34,935 --> 00:53:36,225
No strays.

854
00:53:36,260 --> 00:53:39,940
Hold up your wrist.

855
00:53:39,975 --> 00:53:41,180
No grailband.

856
00:53:41,215 --> 00:53:45,265
Like me.

857
00:53:45,300 --> 00:53:47,100
Are you "Sam?"

858
00:53:48,980 --> 00:53:50,305
I'm Matt Ellman.

859
00:53:50,340 --> 00:53:51,900
A caretaker told me to find you.

860
00:53:51,935 --> 00:53:54,100
Male or female?

861
00:53:54,135 --> 00:53:55,545
A woman,

862
00:53:55,580 --> 00:53:57,460
While I was in Pizarro's camp.

863
00:53:59,612 --> 00:54:01,625
Pizarro.

864
00:54:01,660 --> 00:54:03,665
So he is waiting for us.

865
00:54:03,700 --> 00:54:06,460
We ambushed
some conquistadors upstream.

866
00:54:06,495 --> 00:54:07,985
They were chasing him.

867
00:54:08,020 --> 00:54:09,780
They say the enemy
of my enemy

868
00:54:09,815 --> 00:54:11,865
Is my friend.

869
00:54:11,900 --> 00:54:13,340
Are you my friend,
Mr. Ellman?

870
00:54:13,375 --> 00:54:14,985
Maybe,

871
00:54:15,020 --> 00:54:16,540
Once I get to know you.

872
00:54:18,052 --> 00:54:19,425
My apologies.

873
00:54:19,460 --> 00:54:21,820
I have been remiss
in my introductions.

874
00:54:21,855 --> 00:54:24,180
Well, you've met
our chief of marines,

875
00:54:24,215 --> 00:54:25,825
Youseff mbaye.

876
00:54:25,860 --> 00:54:28,840
Mademoiselle fabarge,

877
00:54:28,875 --> 00:54:31,785
My chief
engineer,

878
00:54:31,820 --> 00:54:35,425
And this lovely
creature,

879
00:54:35,460 --> 00:54:36,940
This is
Allegra Braccioforte...

880
00:54:39,100 --> 00:54:42,665
My diplomatic liaison.

881
00:54:42,700 --> 00:54:45,820
And I am the owner and operator
of this fabulous riverboat,

882
00:54:45,855 --> 00:54:47,545
The not-for-hire.

883
00:54:47,580 --> 00:54:50,460
Captain Samuel Clemens,
at your service.

884
00:54:50,495 --> 00:54:52,477
Samuel Clemens?

885
00:54:52,512 --> 00:54:55,246
As in Mark Twain?

886
00:54:55,281 --> 00:54:57,850
Guilty as charged.

887
00:55:09,860 --> 00:55:11,665
Impressive.

888
00:55:11,700 --> 00:55:13,745
You don't look impressed.

889
00:55:13,780 --> 00:55:16,460
Frankly, you remind me
of a dyspeptic cat,

890
00:55:16,495 --> 00:55:18,345
Like you swallowed
somethin',

891
00:55:18,380 --> 00:55:19,945
And you're about to
cough it back up.

892
00:55:19,980 --> 00:55:23,540
I think, meeting you,
it's made it all hit home...

893
00:55:23,575 --> 00:55:27,420
Mark Twain giving me
a tour of his riverboat.

894
00:55:29,820 --> 00:55:32,385
This place...

895
00:55:32,420 --> 00:55:35,580
It's not just a dream,
is it?

896
00:55:35,615 --> 00:55:38,197
We really are dead.

897
00:55:38,232 --> 00:55:40,745
Dead and reborn.

898
00:55:40,780 --> 00:55:43,740
I woke up here
five years ago.

899
00:55:43,775 --> 00:55:44,985
If I am dead,

900
00:55:45,020 --> 00:55:48,100
Then this is
the longest dream ever.

901
00:55:50,232 --> 00:55:52,225
Millions,

902
00:55:52,260 --> 00:55:53,985
Or perhaps billions
of people

903
00:55:54,020 --> 00:55:57,945
From every epoch
of human history,

904
00:55:57,980 --> 00:56:01,500
Reborn along the banks
of a seemingly endless river.

905
00:56:03,940 --> 00:56:06,300
Basic needs all provided for...

906
00:56:06,335 --> 00:56:08,317
But no children...

907
00:56:08,352 --> 00:56:10,886
No old people...

908
00:56:10,921 --> 00:56:13,385
No civilization.

909
00:56:13,420 --> 00:56:15,820
The question,
Mr. Ellman, is, why?

910
00:56:15,855 --> 00:56:19,020
What is the point
of it all?

911
00:56:19,055 --> 00:56:20,825
Is it a chance to atone?

912
00:56:20,860 --> 00:56:23,120
For what we screwed up
in life?

913
00:56:23,155 --> 00:56:25,345
Life is
a considerable test.

914
00:56:25,380 --> 00:56:26,820
Having endured
its random cruelties

915
00:56:26,855 --> 00:56:28,105
For 75 years,

916
00:56:28,140 --> 00:56:31,020
I see no reason
for a make-up exam.

917
00:56:32,620 --> 00:56:34,500
Do you have
a better explanation?

918
00:56:34,535 --> 00:56:36,145
Nope.

919
00:56:36,180 --> 00:56:38,865
But I do intend to find one.

920
00:56:38,900 --> 00:56:40,500
That's why I built
the not-for-hire

921
00:56:40,535 --> 00:56:42,545
In the first place.

922
00:56:42,580 --> 00:56:44,060
You didn't build it.
You stole it!

923
00:56:44,095 --> 00:56:45,625
I earned this ship.

924
00:56:45,660 --> 00:56:47,460
I found
the raw materials,

925
00:56:47,495 --> 00:56:49,105
The engineers,

926
00:56:49,140 --> 00:56:50,840
Convinced Pizarro
to provide the labour.

927
00:56:50,875 --> 00:56:52,540
Yeah, by telling him
he could use it

928
00:56:52,575 --> 00:56:53,980
To conquer the world.

929
00:56:55,260 --> 00:56:56,825
That was a good trick, huh?

930
00:56:56,860 --> 00:56:59,340
The ship and the girl
all at once.

931
00:56:59,375 --> 00:57:00,697
"the girl?"

932
00:57:00,732 --> 00:57:01,985
Allegra.

933
00:57:02,020 --> 00:57:04,180
She used to be
Pizarro's woman,

934
00:57:04,215 --> 00:57:06,340
Until Sam...

935
00:57:06,375 --> 00:57:08,025
Won her heart.

936
00:57:08,060 --> 00:57:10,065
Pizarro was not happy.

937
00:57:10,100 --> 00:57:13,100
The man takes his grudges
very seriously.

938
00:57:17,340 --> 00:57:20,220
So, why are we
on this journey?

939
00:57:20,255 --> 00:57:22,220
Every river has its source.

940
00:57:22,255 --> 00:57:23,545
I'm convinced

941
00:57:23,580 --> 00:57:25,580
That, at the source of
this particular river,

942
00:57:25,615 --> 00:57:27,905
We shall find its creators,

943
00:57:27,940 --> 00:57:31,980
And, hence, those responsible
for our new existence.

944
00:57:32,015 --> 00:57:33,620
So, you're going to go
to the "source,"

945
00:57:33,655 --> 00:57:35,545
Find the gods, or God,

946
00:57:35,580 --> 00:57:37,640
Or little green men
that made this place,

947
00:57:37,675 --> 00:57:39,700
And force them to give you
an explanation?

948
00:57:39,735 --> 00:57:41,385
That's the plan.

949
00:57:41,420 --> 00:57:45,780
And, you, my friend,
you're gonna make it possible.

950
00:58:01,340 --> 00:58:02,740
They've spotted the ship!

951
00:58:02,775 --> 00:58:04,837
It's coming upriver!

952
00:58:04,872 --> 00:58:06,900
It won't be long now.

953
00:58:24,060 --> 00:58:28,300
El Adelantado,
they are 10 miles out,

954
00:58:28,335 --> 00:58:30,665
Moving dead slow
in deep water.

955
00:58:30,700 --> 00:58:34,660
Does he think
he can just steam past?

956
00:58:34,695 --> 00:58:35,660
Well, let's hope
he tries.

957
00:58:35,695 --> 00:58:36,585
He can't get by

958
00:58:36,620 --> 00:58:37,900
Without coming in range
of our weapons.

959
00:58:37,935 --> 00:58:39,517
You're surprisingly
self-confident

960
00:58:39,552 --> 00:58:41,100
For a man who was
just defeated

961
00:58:41,135 --> 00:58:42,897
By an aboriginal army

962
00:58:42,932 --> 00:58:44,625
And a man on foot.

963
00:58:44,660 --> 00:58:47,820
It wasn't my men who turned
and ran like little girls,

964
00:58:47,855 --> 00:58:50,220
I can assure you
of that.

965
00:58:53,860 --> 00:58:55,860
That's the channel where
Youseff saved my butt.

966
00:58:55,895 --> 00:58:58,025
It had a strong current,

967
00:58:58,060 --> 00:59:00,220
So it probably joins
back up to the main river

968
00:59:00,255 --> 00:59:03,100
Somewhere here...
Above the fort.

969
00:59:05,140 --> 00:59:06,500
Well, it's a riverboat...

970
00:59:06,535 --> 00:59:08,260
Only draws three feet.

971
00:59:08,295 --> 00:59:09,585
Just might work.

972
00:59:09,620 --> 00:59:11,225
So now, if I do this,

973
00:59:11,260 --> 00:59:13,820
How do I know you'll keep
your end of the bargain

974
00:59:13,855 --> 00:59:15,300
And help me find Jessie?

975
00:59:15,335 --> 00:59:17,425
You don't.

976
00:59:17,460 --> 00:59:19,980
It's a quandary,
I know,

977
00:59:20,015 --> 00:59:22,477
But... Look
at this face.

978
00:59:22,512 --> 00:59:24,940
Would this face
lie to you?

979
00:59:24,975 --> 00:59:26,237
In a heartbeat.

980
00:59:27,500 --> 00:59:29,260
It's true...
I am a habitual mendicant,

981
00:59:29,295 --> 00:59:31,577
But I pay my debts,

982
00:59:31,612 --> 00:59:33,825
Not because I'm honest,

983
00:59:33,860 --> 00:59:36,620
But because I dislike intensely
being obliged to another man.

984
00:59:36,655 --> 00:59:38,417
So, if you give me
your assistance

985
00:59:38,452 --> 00:59:40,180
You will have my help
in return,

986
00:59:40,215 --> 00:59:41,620
Measure for measure.

987
00:59:43,220 --> 00:59:46,620
And the others?
The ones back in Pizarro's camp?

988
00:59:46,655 --> 00:59:47,865
What about them?

989
00:59:47,900 --> 00:59:52,220
I'm afraid they will have to
look out for themselves.

990
00:59:52,255 --> 00:59:53,705
It strikes me, Burton,

991
00:59:53,740 --> 00:59:57,420
That trusting you
could be a serious error.

992
00:59:57,455 --> 00:59:58,977
That so?

993
00:59:59,012 --> 01:00:00,465
How can I be certain

994
01:00:00,500 --> 01:00:02,780
That you're not
an agent of the enemy?

995
01:00:02,815 --> 01:00:04,517
Certainty is a luxury,
my friend,

996
01:00:04,552 --> 01:00:05,986
Along with clarity,
faith, sanity...

997
01:00:06,021 --> 01:00:07,385
All those
other foolish notions

998
01:00:07,420 --> 01:00:08,460
We clung to in
our previous existence.

999
01:00:08,495 --> 01:00:10,460
Do not tempt fate,
my friend...

1000
01:00:10,495 --> 01:00:11,465
Look out!

1001
01:00:18,860 --> 01:00:20,825
You are a mad woman.

1002
01:00:20,860 --> 01:00:22,745
Why do you
throw your life away?

1003
01:00:22,780 --> 01:00:25,100
You killed her husband
the day you rode in.

1004
01:00:25,135 --> 01:00:26,517
Ah, si, si...

1005
01:00:26,552 --> 01:00:27,865
I'd forgotten.

1006
01:00:27,900 --> 01:00:30,660
It was of such
little significance.

1007
01:00:32,060 --> 01:00:34,500
Burn her at the stake.

1008
01:00:34,540 --> 01:00:39,145
No!

1009
01:01:06,540 --> 01:01:08,065
Youseff?

1010
01:01:08,100 --> 01:01:11,180
When you were alive,
you were a soldier, right?

1011
01:01:11,215 --> 01:01:13,140
I was a taxi driver.

1012
01:01:13,175 --> 01:01:14,425
In Dakar.

1013
01:01:14,460 --> 01:01:15,945
My brother
was the soldier.

1014
01:01:15,980 --> 01:01:19,180
He was a sergeant
in the tirailleurs senegalais,

1015
01:01:19,215 --> 01:01:22,020
But I had a family,
so I stayed home.

1016
01:01:22,055 --> 01:01:23,420
Then what's with the hat?

1017
01:01:24,900 --> 01:01:28,425
Allah gave me a second life.

1018
01:01:28,460 --> 01:01:31,300
What is the point living it
the same way I did my first?

1019
01:01:31,335 --> 01:01:33,700
So I am a soldier...

1020
01:01:33,735 --> 01:01:34,665
Now,

1021
01:01:34,700 --> 01:01:37,060
And I've been one
for six years.

1022
01:01:37,095 --> 01:01:38,497
Why?

1023
01:01:38,532 --> 01:01:39,865
Tell me,

1024
01:01:39,900 --> 01:01:42,540
Does Sam's plan have
a chance in hell of working?

1025
01:01:42,575 --> 01:01:44,625
Insha'Allah...

1026
01:01:44,660 --> 01:01:47,585
It is in the hands of Allah,

1027
01:01:47,620 --> 01:01:50,500
Or whatever he is called
in this place.

1028
01:02:00,140 --> 01:02:02,540
Three years
to build this boat...

1029
01:02:02,575 --> 01:02:04,905
Another two years of runnin'...

1030
01:02:04,940 --> 01:02:06,900
It all comes down to this.

1031
01:02:06,935 --> 01:02:09,900
It's not good
to worry so much.

1032
01:02:12,380 --> 01:02:13,825
The rich and powerful
of venice

1033
01:02:13,860 --> 01:02:16,420
Must've lined the grand
canal outside your door.

1034
01:02:16,455 --> 01:02:18,025
Too bourgeois.

1035
01:02:18,060 --> 01:02:19,920
I had an apprentice
arrange it

1036
01:02:19,955 --> 01:02:21,780
So my lovers
never saw each other.

1037
01:02:21,815 --> 01:02:24,097
Each could
delude himself

1038
01:02:24,132 --> 01:02:26,380
Into believing
I was his...

1039
01:02:26,415 --> 01:02:28,985
And his alone.

1040
01:02:29,020 --> 01:02:32,905
I suffer no such delusions,
my dear.

1041
01:02:32,940 --> 01:02:35,500
I'm content to be among
the unwashed multitudes.

1042
01:02:36,940 --> 01:02:38,740
I was thinking...

1043
01:02:40,260 --> 01:02:42,025
Perhaps I should
get closer

1044
01:02:42,060 --> 01:02:43,860
To our new friend,
senor Ellman.

1045
01:02:43,895 --> 01:02:45,585
Take a peek,

1046
01:02:45,620 --> 01:02:48,060
See if he has
something to hide.

1047
01:02:48,095 --> 01:02:50,500
Are you trying
to make me jealous?

1048
01:02:50,535 --> 01:02:51,740
Are you trying
to pretend

1049
01:02:51,775 --> 01:02:53,065
It's not working?

1050
01:02:53,100 --> 01:02:57,060
Let us endeavor to get past
the spaniard first.

1051
01:02:58,220 --> 01:03:01,900
And then we can discuss
your machiavellian designs

1052
01:03:01,935 --> 01:03:03,540
On young Mr. Ellman.

1053
01:03:03,575 --> 01:03:05,105
Machiavelli...

1054
01:03:05,140 --> 01:03:08,180
Now, there was a man
who knew how to treat a lady.

1055
01:03:08,215 --> 01:03:10,220
Incorrigible.

1056
01:03:17,020 --> 01:03:18,780
Matthew?

1057
01:03:22,060 --> 01:03:23,820
Matthew.

1058
01:03:25,220 --> 01:03:26,980
Matthew...

1059
01:03:28,620 --> 01:03:30,540
Matt... Matthew!

1060
01:03:34,820 --> 01:03:36,025
Matthew.

1061
01:03:39,380 --> 01:03:41,025
What do you want?

1062
01:03:41,060 --> 01:03:42,760
Burton is still alive.

1063
01:03:42,795 --> 01:03:44,425
You have to stop him.

1064
01:03:44,460 --> 01:03:48,260
I'm not good at taking orders,
never have been.

1065
01:03:48,295 --> 01:03:49,705
Kill Burton.

1066
01:03:49,740 --> 01:03:51,160
It is the only way

1067
01:03:51,195 --> 01:03:52,580
To save Jessica.

1068
01:03:52,615 --> 01:03:53,625
Look.

1069
01:03:53,660 --> 01:03:55,340
You want me to kill someone?

1070
01:03:55,375 --> 01:03:56,465
I'm going to need

1071
01:03:56,500 --> 01:03:57,620
A little more
information.

1072
01:04:03,940 --> 01:04:05,145
Great.

1073
01:04:05,180 --> 01:04:06,860
Really helpful.

1074
01:04:21,980 --> 01:04:23,820
What is that?

1075
01:04:23,855 --> 01:04:24,905
That...

1076
01:04:24,940 --> 01:04:27,220
Is none of
your damn business.

1077
01:04:38,660 --> 01:04:39,825
The engine room was locked,

1078
01:04:39,860 --> 01:04:41,540
But there he was,
nosing around.

1079
01:04:41,575 --> 01:04:43,097
You have to forgive
poor amelie.

1080
01:04:43,132 --> 01:04:44,620
She doesn't
like strange noses

1081
01:04:44,655 --> 01:04:46,225
In her private places.

1082
01:04:46,260 --> 01:04:47,785
Excuse me,
but I don't open my door

1083
01:04:47,820 --> 01:04:49,540
To every man
who's willing to pay the price.

1084
01:04:49,575 --> 01:04:51,225
Ladies! Ladies.

1085
01:04:51,260 --> 01:04:53,505
Now, back to
the subject at hand.

1086
01:04:53,540 --> 01:04:55,980
Yeah. Like what's that thing
powering your ship?

1087
01:04:56,015 --> 01:04:59,185
It was a gift...

1088
01:04:59,220 --> 01:05:00,900
From one of our protectors.

1089
01:05:00,935 --> 01:05:03,140
The woman caretaker?

1090
01:05:03,175 --> 01:05:04,785
Yes.

1091
01:05:04,820 --> 01:05:06,305
She bequeathed it to me

1092
01:05:06,340 --> 01:05:09,580
In exchange for some...
As-of-yet unnamed future favour.

1093
01:05:09,615 --> 01:05:11,717
Helping you, perhaps?

1094
01:05:11,752 --> 01:05:13,785
As to what it is?

1095
01:05:13,820 --> 01:05:17,860
Mademoiselle fabarge
has her theories.

1096
01:05:17,895 --> 01:05:19,985
It might be
a fusion reactor,

1097
01:05:20,020 --> 01:05:22,580
Fueled by the hydrogen
in the water.

1098
01:05:22,615 --> 01:05:24,185
That thing is nuclear?

1099
01:05:24,220 --> 01:05:25,865
You see now
why it's important

1100
01:05:25,900 --> 01:05:27,840
That this ship not fall
into the wrong hands?

1101
01:05:27,875 --> 01:05:29,780
How do we know this one
isn't the wrong hands?

1102
01:05:29,815 --> 01:05:30,985
Why are we trusting him?

1103
01:05:32,655 --> 01:05:34,117
We are in position.

1104
01:05:36,121 --> 01:05:38,020
Time to get to work.

1105
01:05:39,380 --> 01:05:41,180
As to whether or not
we can trust you,

1106
01:05:41,215 --> 01:05:42,425
Mr. Ellman,

1107
01:05:42,460 --> 01:05:43,820
I suppose
we shall see...

1108
01:05:43,855 --> 01:05:45,900
Directly.

1109
01:05:52,940 --> 01:05:54,140
Help me!

1110
01:05:54,175 --> 01:05:57,065
Somebody, help!

1111
01:05:57,100 --> 01:05:59,300
They're going to
burn her at the stake!

1112
01:06:00,855 --> 01:06:03,100
It is time.

1113
01:06:05,575 --> 01:06:07,117
Time for what?

1114
01:06:07,152 --> 01:06:08,660
Time to be brave.

1115
01:06:11,820 --> 01:06:13,300
Don't you think
we need a little help?

1116
01:06:13,335 --> 01:06:15,377
All the slaves
enjoy complaining,

1117
01:06:15,412 --> 01:06:17,420
But none will
risk their lives.

1118
01:06:18,700 --> 01:06:20,400
There's a friend
of Matt's...

1119
01:06:20,435 --> 01:06:22,100
In prison,
his name's Simon.

1120
01:06:22,135 --> 01:06:23,705
Then bring him.

1121
01:06:23,740 --> 01:06:27,700
The spaniard's lust for death
must be answered.

1122
01:06:53,220 --> 01:06:54,860
Sounding.

1123
01:06:59,460 --> 01:07:01,020
Half Twain.

1124
01:07:01,055 --> 01:07:02,545
Six feet?

1125
01:07:02,580 --> 01:07:05,220
I've stepped
in deeper puddles.

1126
01:07:19,695 --> 01:07:21,585
The grailstone...

1127
01:07:21,620 --> 01:07:23,140
That's where I was held
in the cage.

1128
01:07:25,060 --> 01:07:26,780
Somebody, help me!

1129
01:07:26,815 --> 01:07:28,500
No!

1130
01:07:28,535 --> 01:07:31,105
No! No!

1131
01:07:35,020 --> 01:07:37,420
Something
interests you, english?

1132
01:07:39,540 --> 01:07:43,060
Thinhe t fox
has outfoxed the hounds.

1133
01:07:51,300 --> 01:07:53,340
Clemens...

1134
01:07:53,380 --> 01:07:55,025
On my ship!

1135
01:07:55,060 --> 01:07:57,065
He's in behind us.

1136
01:07:57,100 --> 01:07:59,460
Conquistadors!

1137
01:07:59,495 --> 01:08:01,820
Reposition the catapults!

1138
01:08:01,855 --> 01:08:04,145
Now! Now!

1139
01:08:04,180 --> 01:08:06,540
We're under attack!
We're under attack!

1140
01:08:06,575 --> 01:08:08,900
Go! Go! Go! Go!
We're under attack!

1141
01:08:08,935 --> 01:08:11,105
Go! Go! Go! Go!
Go!

1142
01:08:11,140 --> 01:08:13,500
Watch out, watch out,
watch out!

1143
01:08:17,420 --> 01:08:19,140
Damn! That was cool.

1144
01:08:19,175 --> 01:08:20,197
Where's Matt?

1145
01:08:20,232 --> 01:08:21,185
Matthew's gone.

1146
01:08:21,220 --> 01:08:23,425
El hefe's about to
roast Deborah,

1147
01:08:23,460 --> 01:08:25,860
And three of us are going to
take on Pizarro's army.

1148
01:08:25,895 --> 01:08:27,145
Sound fun?

1149
01:08:27,180 --> 01:08:28,460
No, that doesn't
sound like fun.

1150
01:08:29,415 --> 01:08:30,497
Come on!

1151
01:08:30,532 --> 01:08:31,580
Oh, geez!

1152
01:08:31,620 --> 01:08:33,140
Come back here,
you cowards!

1153
01:08:36,340 --> 01:08:37,220
Come!

1154
01:08:38,780 --> 01:08:40,660
To the front!

1155
01:08:45,860 --> 01:08:48,340
Please, release
our friend now.

1156
01:09:01,460 --> 01:09:03,540
Prepare your soul.

1157
01:09:12,700 --> 01:09:14,225
I am Tomoe Gozen,

1158
01:09:14,260 --> 01:09:16,820
Swordswoman
of the minamoto clan,

1159
01:09:16,855 --> 01:09:19,025
Champion, consort,

1160
01:09:19,060 --> 01:09:21,340
And war captain
to Kiso Yoshinaka.

1161
01:09:21,375 --> 01:09:23,865
I bow to no man.

1162
01:09:23,900 --> 01:09:27,740
Please,
release our friend now.

1163
01:09:27,775 --> 01:09:29,465
Kill her.

1164
01:09:29,500 --> 01:09:32,700
Kill them all.

1165
01:09:59,220 --> 01:10:00,380
Stop, stop, stop, stop.

1166
01:10:00,415 --> 01:10:02,237
We have to keep moving.

1167
01:10:02,272 --> 01:10:04,025
Matthew, you cannot help.

1168
01:10:04,060 --> 01:10:06,220
We have to
get past the fort.

1169
01:10:08,980 --> 01:10:10,420
I got to borrow this.

1170
01:10:10,455 --> 01:10:12,437
Matthew!

1171
01:10:24,580 --> 01:10:25,905
Let's go!

1172
01:10:25,940 --> 01:10:27,820
But we're not fighting?

1173
01:10:27,855 --> 01:10:29,940
Not his battles.

1174
01:10:46,180 --> 01:10:47,265
Three-quarters Twain.

1175
01:10:47,300 --> 01:10:49,100
It's getting deeper,
and we're past the camp.

1176
01:10:49,135 --> 01:10:50,820
Start the engines.
Get us out of here.

1177
01:10:50,855 --> 01:10:51,980
Not yet. We have
an agreement

1178
01:10:52,015 --> 01:10:53,065
With Mr. Ellman.

1179
01:10:53,100 --> 01:10:54,680
You really
meant all that?

1180
01:10:54,715 --> 01:10:56,225
I thought
you had sense.

1181
01:10:56,260 --> 01:10:58,420
Sometimes, I don't know
why I tolerate you.

1182
01:10:58,455 --> 01:11:00,980
Well, we know
it's not for my cooking.

1183
01:11:01,015 --> 01:11:02,540
Burton, get your men!

1184
01:11:02,575 --> 01:11:03,625
Burton!

1185
01:11:04,980 --> 01:11:08,440
Never trust a man
who eats blood pudding.

1186
01:11:08,475 --> 01:11:11,900
Santiago y cierra!
Conquistadores! Vamos!

1187
01:11:23,340 --> 01:11:25,260
I'm a college professor.
What am I doing here?

1188
01:11:29,660 --> 01:11:30,860
Oh... Antonio!
Look out!

1189
01:11:30,895 --> 01:11:32,477
Antonio!

1190
01:11:33,781 --> 01:11:34,980
No!

1191
01:11:36,180 --> 01:11:37,700
Get him out of here!

1192
01:12:21,020 --> 01:12:23,585
You never told me
you were a samurai.

1193
01:12:23,620 --> 01:12:26,500
A samurai does not talk,
a samurai fights.

1194
01:12:26,535 --> 01:12:28,140
Conquistadores!

1195
01:12:37,075 --> 01:12:38,605
Deborah!

1196
01:12:43,052 --> 01:12:45,085
Encore!

1197
01:12:45,120 --> 01:12:47,400
Mr. Youseff!

1198
01:12:47,435 --> 01:12:49,257
Vite! Vite!

1199
01:12:49,292 --> 01:12:51,080
Wait, wait! Go!

1200
01:12:51,115 --> 01:12:53,405
Go!

1201
01:13:04,995 --> 01:13:08,217
Youseff.

1202
01:13:11,440 --> 01:13:13,620
You guys
seen Deborah?

1203
01:13:13,655 --> 01:13:15,765
You guys seen
Deborah?

1204
01:13:15,800 --> 01:13:19,160
You know,
I think we did it.

1205
01:13:19,195 --> 01:13:21,317
I think we did it.

1206
01:13:23,475 --> 01:13:25,965
Hey, guys.

1207
01:13:26,000 --> 01:13:27,880
Bet you didn't think
I was coming back.

1208
01:13:27,915 --> 01:13:29,365
You're such a dumbass,

1209
01:13:29,400 --> 01:13:31,040
You're not even smart
enough to save yourself.

1210
01:13:40,200 --> 01:13:42,720
As many times
as I've seen this,

1211
01:13:42,755 --> 01:13:44,817
I never get used to it.

1212
01:13:44,852 --> 01:13:46,880
We're not supposed to.

1213
01:13:48,800 --> 01:13:50,760
Is that your friend?

1214
01:13:50,795 --> 01:13:52,200
I hope so.

1215
01:13:52,240 --> 01:13:56,040
I sure as hell
don't want her as an enemy.

1216
01:13:59,920 --> 01:14:01,240
Behind you!

1217
01:14:32,720 --> 01:14:34,640
I am nothat easy to.

1218
01:14:39,880 --> 01:14:41,840
Sure ya are.

1219
01:14:41,875 --> 01:14:43,537
Clemens...

1220
01:14:43,572 --> 01:14:45,200
Hello, Francisco.

1221
01:14:45,235 --> 01:14:47,365
Coward.

1222
01:14:47,400 --> 01:14:50,405
In the back?

1223
01:14:50,440 --> 01:14:53,000
I find, if you must shoot
a dangerous animal,

1224
01:14:53,035 --> 01:14:54,377
It's best to do it by surprise

1225
01:14:54,412 --> 01:14:55,720
And from
a considerable distance.

1226
01:15:02,651 --> 01:15:05,285
Strange...

1227
01:15:05,320 --> 01:15:07,720
Thought I would enjoy that.

1228
01:15:09,320 --> 01:15:12,440
You don't see this
every day.

1229
01:15:49,320 --> 01:15:51,780
Burton escaped.

1230
01:15:51,815 --> 01:15:54,205
Gee, sorry...

1231
01:15:54,240 --> 01:15:56,700
I was a little busy
trying not to get stabbed.

1232
01:15:56,735 --> 01:15:59,160
As long as Burton lives,
none of you are safe.

1233
01:16:01,080 --> 01:16:03,640
The others don't see you.

1234
01:16:03,675 --> 01:16:05,880
This is a dream.

1235
01:16:05,915 --> 01:16:08,485
A message.

1236
01:16:08,520 --> 01:16:11,160
Delivered
to the wrong person.

1237
01:16:11,195 --> 01:16:13,725
I'm not a killer.

1238
01:16:13,760 --> 01:16:16,485
Why are you here,
Matthew Ellman?

1239
01:16:16,520 --> 01:16:19,245
Have you asked yourself
that question?

1240
01:16:19,280 --> 01:16:22,280
I'm still trying to figure out
what "here" is.

1241
01:16:22,315 --> 01:16:24,737
When this Riverworld
was created,

1242
01:16:24,772 --> 01:16:26,766
We believed
it could be a place

1243
01:16:26,801 --> 01:16:28,760
For your people
to be reborn,

1244
01:16:28,795 --> 01:16:30,565
A place for atonement,

1245
01:16:30,600 --> 01:16:33,560
A second chance
to achieve perfection.

1246
01:16:33,595 --> 01:16:35,777
But there are
a few among us

1247
01:16:35,812 --> 01:16:37,706
Who believe
we have failed,

1248
01:16:37,741 --> 01:16:39,565
That you are not worthy,

1249
01:16:39,600 --> 01:16:41,840
And so this world
must be destroyed.

1250
01:16:41,875 --> 01:16:43,880
You said "created."

1251
01:16:43,915 --> 01:16:45,325
By who?

1252
01:16:45,360 --> 01:16:48,040
We cannot act directly
on your behalf.

1253
01:16:48,075 --> 01:16:50,317
Our laws forbid it.

1254
01:16:50,352 --> 01:16:52,560
But some have
seen fit

1255
01:16:52,595 --> 01:16:54,537
To ignore our laws

1256
01:16:54,572 --> 01:16:56,445
And interfere...

1257
01:16:56,480 --> 01:16:59,720
To choose champions
among the awakened,

1258
01:16:59,755 --> 01:17:01,617
People
who they can use

1259
01:17:01,652 --> 01:17:03,445
To serve
their own ends.

1260
01:17:03,480 --> 01:17:06,365
Burton is the champion
of the salvationists,

1261
01:17:06,400 --> 01:17:08,960
A tool they intend to use
to destroy the Riverworld.

1262
01:17:08,995 --> 01:17:11,680
And I'm your champion?

1263
01:17:11,715 --> 01:17:13,777
Yes.

1264
01:17:13,812 --> 01:17:15,826
You...

1265
01:17:15,861 --> 01:17:17,850
Sam...

1266
01:17:17,885 --> 01:17:19,702
Jessica.

1267
01:17:19,737 --> 01:17:21,485
Jessica?

1268
01:17:21,520 --> 01:17:23,420
Jessica is...

1269
01:17:23,455 --> 01:17:25,285
Our hope,

1270
01:17:25,320 --> 01:17:28,320
But she is in great danger.

1271
01:17:31,320 --> 01:17:33,400
Stop Burton.

1272
01:17:33,435 --> 01:17:35,917
For you...

1273
01:17:35,952 --> 01:17:37,876
For Jessica...

1274
01:17:37,911 --> 01:17:39,800
For all of us.

1275
01:18:03,120 --> 01:18:06,365
Hey... You'll be okay.

1276
01:18:06,400 --> 01:18:10,880
Just, maybe cut back
on the swashbuckling a bit?

1277
01:18:10,915 --> 01:18:13,817
I'll trade the swash
for the swish.

1278
01:18:13,852 --> 01:18:16,720
Sorry...
I couldn't resist.

1279
01:18:16,755 --> 01:18:18,840
It means
you're feeling better.

1280
01:18:20,960 --> 01:18:23,160
I'm going to go
check on the others,

1281
01:18:23,195 --> 01:18:25,120
But I'll be back
soon, okay?

1282
01:18:25,155 --> 01:18:27,920
I'm not going anywhere.

1283
01:18:46,320 --> 01:18:48,485
All right, gentlemen...
and lady...

1284
01:18:48,520 --> 01:18:52,040
Let's fire this old gal up,
see where she'll take us.

1285
01:18:52,075 --> 01:18:53,520
That... Is
an excellent idea.

1286
01:18:53,555 --> 01:18:54,845
Who the hell are you?

1287
01:18:54,880 --> 01:18:57,040
Burton.
His name is Burton.

1288
01:19:03,160 --> 01:19:04,920
I don't believe
we've been introduced.

1289
01:19:04,955 --> 01:19:06,680
Captain sir
Richard Francis Burton.

1290
01:19:06,715 --> 01:19:07,720
My friends
call me "dick".

1291
01:19:07,755 --> 01:19:10,205
Burton, the explorer?

1292
01:19:10,240 --> 01:19:11,845
Yeah, I read
one of your books.

1293
01:19:11,880 --> 01:19:14,280
It was amateurish,
unnecessarily crude,

1294
01:19:14,315 --> 01:19:16,680
And pathetically
self-congratulatory.

1295
01:19:16,715 --> 01:19:18,325
Clemens, I'm confused.

1296
01:19:18,360 --> 01:19:20,440
Are you talking about
my work or yours?

1297
01:19:21,995 --> 01:19:23,845
You again.

1298
01:19:23,880 --> 01:19:25,920
You want to deal
with me, fine,

1299
01:19:25,955 --> 01:19:27,317
But, first,
let him go.

1300
01:19:27,352 --> 01:19:28,680
He has no part
in this.

1301
01:19:28,715 --> 01:19:30,360
Why, certainly.

1302
01:19:44,600 --> 01:19:47,720
You see, Mr. Ellman,
I can be quite reasonable.

1303
01:19:47,755 --> 01:19:50,840
Now, Mr. Clemens, if
you'll set down your weapon

1304
01:19:50,875 --> 01:19:53,577
We can discuss the terms
of your surrender.

1305
01:19:53,612 --> 01:19:56,280
"Surrender" is not
in my vast vocabulary.

1306
01:19:56,315 --> 01:19:57,365
How about "bollocks"?

1307
01:19:57,400 --> 01:19:59,080
Is that in your vast vocabulary?

1308
01:19:59,115 --> 01:20:00,205
Bollocks?

1309
01:20:01,815 --> 01:20:03,907
Ah! Son of a bitch!

1310
01:20:03,942 --> 01:20:06,000
Not... A good idea.

1311
01:20:06,035 --> 01:20:07,965
You, sir...

1312
01:20:08,000 --> 01:20:09,520
Are a most despicable example

1313
01:20:09,555 --> 01:20:11,325
Of humankind.

1314
01:20:11,360 --> 01:20:12,445
Why, thank you.
Mr. Ellman...

1315
01:20:12,480 --> 01:20:14,160
I'm disappointed.
I saved your life once.

1316
01:20:14,195 --> 01:20:16,117
Where's the gratitude?

1317
01:20:16,152 --> 01:20:18,005
I'll send flowers.

1318
01:20:18,040 --> 01:20:20,480
Roses, I find,
work for any occasion,

1319
01:20:20,515 --> 01:20:21,845
Although now
I've secured this ship,

1320
01:20:21,880 --> 01:20:24,520
Keeping you alive doesn't
have the same urgency

1321
01:20:24,555 --> 01:20:26,040
That it once did.

1322
01:20:30,040 --> 01:20:31,760
Jessie... Jessie?

1323
01:20:33,792 --> 01:20:35,576
Jessie...

1324
01:20:35,611 --> 01:20:37,360
Jess...

1325
01:20:39,640 --> 01:20:41,160
Jessie?

1326
01:20:41,195 --> 01:20:42,645
"Jessie."

1327
01:20:42,680 --> 01:20:44,845
Yes, thank you
for reminding me.

1328
01:20:44,880 --> 01:20:47,240
She... Gave me a
message to give to you.

1329
01:20:47,275 --> 01:20:48,720
Now, what was it?

1330
01:20:48,755 --> 01:20:49,965
You bastard.

1331
01:20:50,000 --> 01:20:51,760
No, that wasn't it.

1332
01:20:51,795 --> 01:20:53,485
Now I remember.

1333
01:20:53,520 --> 01:20:55,245
She said to tell you

1334
01:20:55,280 --> 01:20:56,880
She was in love
with another man,

1335
01:20:56,915 --> 01:20:58,160
And to give you this...

1336
01:21:03,280 --> 01:21:04,480
Matt!

1337
01:21:04,515 --> 01:21:05,680
Matthew!

1338
01:21:29,960 --> 01:21:31,960
Sweep the ship for survivors!

1339
01:21:31,995 --> 01:21:33,457
Prepare to cast off.

1340
01:21:33,492 --> 01:21:34,885
Come on!

1341
01:21:34,920 --> 01:21:38,560
This way.
Salut. I'm amelie.

1342
01:21:38,595 --> 01:21:41,485
Antonio.
Call me tony.

1343
01:21:41,520 --> 01:21:43,920
Thanks for helping me out
back there.

1344
01:21:43,955 --> 01:21:45,720
Show me.

1345
01:21:46,920 --> 01:21:48,205
Lovely.

1346
01:21:48,240 --> 01:21:49,500
Quite lovely.

1347
01:21:49,535 --> 01:21:50,725
And you thought

1348
01:21:50,760 --> 01:21:52,920
I never graduated
from soviet naval academy.

1349
01:21:59,220 --> 01:22:01,900
It should put on
quite a show.

1350
01:22:07,580 --> 01:22:09,620
Sorry, Sam.

1351
01:22:13,220 --> 01:22:16,060
Matthew!

1352
01:22:34,580 --> 01:22:36,860
<i>It was an accident...</i>

1353
01:22:36,895 --> 01:22:38,425
<i>It was an accident...
Okay? Okay?</i>

1354
01:22:38,460 --> 01:22:40,420
<i>You can't keep beating
yourself up over it</i>

1355
01:22:40,455 --> 01:22:42,265
<i>Your entire life.</i>

1356
01:22:42,300 --> 01:22:43,540
<i>Yeah, that's
what everyone says...</i>

1357
01:22:43,580 --> 01:22:45,505
<i>What everyone says...
What everyone says...</i>

1358
01:22:45,540 --> 01:22:48,060
<i>People need to see the truth.
People need to see the truth.</i>

1359
01:22:48,095 --> 01:22:49,260
<i>"forget it.
Put it behind you."</i>

1360
01:22:49,295 --> 01:22:50,785
<i>"put it behind you."</i>

1361
01:22:50,820 --> 01:22:54,180
<i>You owe it to that little girl
to keep showing it to them...</i>

1362
01:22:54,215 --> 01:22:56,277
<i>Otherwise you're
wasting two lives...</i>

1363
01:22:56,312 --> 01:22:58,246
<i>Otherwise you're wasting
two lives.</i>

1364
01:22:58,281 --> 01:23:00,180
How come you know
all the answers?

1365
01:23:00,215 --> 01:23:01,380
You know all
the answers?

1366
01:23:01,415 --> 01:23:03,380
